NIE LOOKING FOR GENERATING OPPORTUNITIES IN SOUTHERN IRELAND

Northern Ireland Electricity is believed to be looking for new
electricity generating opportunities in Southern Ireland, using natural
gas.

The company made a profit of #47.5m. last year and so far has been
immune from the takeover activity affecting UK utilities.

It is exclusively a distribution/sales company, with no current
generation capacity.



