UK GAS REPORT via NewsNet
January 12, 1996

HOUSEHOLD BILLS COULD RISE BY ONE THIRD

Charity Age Concern has estimated that the average household bill could
rise by almost one third this winter because of the bitterly cold
weather and the addition of 8% VAT to domestic gas bills.

The government has a system of cold weather payments for households
which are payable when the temperature falls to freezing for seven
consecutive days.

However, only certain people are eligible for the #8.50 allowance.

To qualify for the payment, recipients must be claiming income support
and either 60 or over and claiming the basic state pension, disabled or
living with a disabled person, or with a dependent child under five.



