INTERNATIONAL ELECTRIC VEHICLE PROGRAMS AND POLICIES
AND THEIR LIKELY CONSEQUENCES

This (GAO) report examines international electric
vehicle development and commercialization programs, and
the likely consequences they will have on the future
for electric vehicles.  The study also encompasses a
review of current barriers to electric vehicle
implementation, field visits in seven nations and the
U.S. to examine electric vehicle programs and policies,
and analyses of electric vehicle effects on economics,
energy, and the environment.

