Multi-Layer Coating Reduces VOC's

Du Pont (Wilmington, DE 19898; Tel 302/774-1000) has been assigned
a patent for a low volatile organic compound (VOC) multi-layer
clear coating.  The process described in US Patent 5,227,201,
issued to Lee R. Harper on July 13, 1993, forms multiple coats of
finishes on a substrate by first applying a color basecoat layer of
pigment-containing acrylic polymer latex.  Before the basecoat is
cured, a clear coat acrylic polymer having crosslinkable groups and
a crosslinking agent in a volatile organic solvent is applied.  The
layers are cured simultaneously.




