REMOTE SENSING AS APPLIED TO POLLUTION MONITORING

This report (from the NTIS Bibliographic Database)
concerns the use of remote sensors to aid in the
monitoring of air and water pollution.  It addresses
the use of lasers, optical radar systems, aerial
photography, and satellite observations.  The report
consists of a collection of abstracts of available
reports, studies, papers, and other documentation, with
references for their acquisition and extensive indexing
to make it easy to find exactly what you want.  It will
be updated to include the latest information available
at the time you place your order.

