January 1996

GAS REBURN TECHNOLOGY TO REDUCE NOx EMISSIONS IN
TANGENTIALLY-FIRED BOILERS [951321]

There are several ways that owners of
tangentially-fired boilers can reduce nitrogen oxides
(NOx) emissions, in order to comply with the Clean Air
Act Amendments of 1990.  This (ABB Combustion
Engineering Services Inc.) report presents and
discusses the development of a close-coupled gas reburn
technology for this purpose.  Close-coupled gas reburn
technology has the potential to be a relatively
lower-cost derivative of standard reburning technology.
A utility scale feasibility, test, and evaluation
program is reported that examines the technology's NOx
reduction capability and its boiler-performance
impacts.

